text: Eugene Roshal (; born 1972) is a Russian software engineer. == Career == Roshal is best known as the developer of: * RAR file format (1993) * WinRAR file archiver (1995) * FAR file manager (1996) RAR is officially owned by his elder brother Alexander, because Eugene Roshal has "no time to concern himself with software development and copyright-related issues at the same time." == References == Category:1972 births Category:Living people Category:Russian Jews Category:Russian computer scientists Category:Software engineers
title: Eugene Roshal
